<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN331-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. uṟaiyūr mutukkūttaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN331">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kallaṟut tiyaṟṟiya valluvark kūval</l>
<l>villēr vāḻkkaic cīṟūr matavali</l>
<l>naṉinal kūrntaṉa ṉāyiṉum paṉimikap</l>
<l>pulleṉ mālai ciṟutī ñeliyuṅ</l>
<l>kallā viṭaiyaṉ pōla kuṟippi</l>
<l>ṉillatu paṭaikkavum valla ṉuḷḷatu</l>
<l>tavaciṟi tāyiṉu mikapala reṉṉā</l>
<l>ṇīṇeṭum panta rūṇmuṟai yūṭṭu</l>
<l>milpoli makaṭūu pōla cilcila</l>
<l>varicaiyi ṉaḷikkavum valla ṉuritiṉiṟ</l>
<l>kāvaṉ maṉṉar kaṭaimukat tukukkum</l>
<l>pōkupali veḷcōṟu pōla</l>
<l>tūvavum vallaṉavaṉ tūvuṅ kālē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Even if the strong man of the little village whose livelihood is the bow for a plough, (2)</l>
<l>with a very brackish well made by cutting off the stones, (1)</l>
<l>is very poor, like an untaught shepherd (3a-c+5ab)</l>
<l>who kindles a little fire by friction on chilly [and] empty evenings, (3d-4)</l>
<l>he is able to create what is not from [his] intention, (6)</l>
<l>and even if there is very little that is there, like a woman </l>
<l>shining in the house, who feeds in [proper] order the whole long arbour</l>
<l>without saying “these [are] many people”, he is able</l>
<l>to bestow according to merit at least a little, (7-10c)</l>
<l>and, like the white rice [that is] the food offering (12)</l>
<l>they suitably shed at the door of the guardian kings, (10d-11) </l>
<l>he is able to shower [gifts], at a time of affluence. (13)   </l>
</lg>
    </div>
